  "What is beat frequency": "",
  "If two tuning forks have frequencies 440 and 444 Hz, beat frequency": "",
  "Beat frequency = |f₁ - f₂|. When two sources of slightly different frequencies interfere, you hear periodic amplitude variations at the beat frequency. The answer is '4 Hz'. The other options — '884 Hz', '442 Hz', and '2 Hz' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": ""
